The paper deals with algorithms for metrical task systems, which are a type of optimization problem in computer science. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces new techniques for combining algorithms, which is a topic in algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL). The paper discusses unfair metrical task systems, which involves game theory and mechanism design (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of randomized algorithms, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
